# Authentication — Google credentials

ALWAYS use `GOOGLE_APPLICATION_CREDENTIALS` for all Google API calls. NEVER use API keys or hardcoded credentials. ADK, Vertex AI SDK, and `google-generativeai` pick up credentials from this env var automatically.

```python
import vertexai
vertexai.init(
    project=os.getenv("GCP_PROJECT_ID"),
    location=os.getenv("VERTEX_AI_LOCATION", "us-central1")
)
# Credentials loaded automatically from GOOGLE_APPLICATION_CREDENTIALS
```

NEVER use `GOOGLE_API_KEY` — always `GOOGLE_APPLICATION_CREDENTIALS`.

# LLM — Gemini 1.5 Flash via Vertex AI

Use Gemini 1.5 Flash for all LLM calls. ADK handles auth automatically.

```python
from google.adk.agents import LlmAgent

agent = LlmAgent(
    name="agent_name",
    model="gemini-1.5-flash",
    instruction="System prompt here...",
    tools=[...],
)
```

# Embeddings — text-embedding-004 (768-dim) via Vertex AI

Always use Vertex AI `text-embedding-004`. Same model locally and in production. Vectors are always 768-dim — pgvector column is `vector(768)`.

```python
import vertexai
from vertexai.language_models import TextEmbeddingModel

vertexai.init(project=os.getenv("GCP_PROJECT_ID"), location=os.getenv("VERTEX_AI_LOCATION"))
model = TextEmbeddingModel.from_pretrained("text-embedding-004")

async def embed_text(text: str) -> list[float]:
    embeddings = model.get_embeddings([text])
    return embeddings[0].values  # always 768-dim
```

NEVER use sentence-transformers or any local embedding model. NEVER use `EMBEDDING_PROVIDER` switching — only Vertex AI. NEVER use Ollama or LiteLLM for this stack.
